  "text": "A related human trait is the need for closure, which has been studied in model based group decision making by Franco et al. [CITATION_1] . A group with high need for closure wants the problem solving process to end up in an unambiguous uncontested outcome. Once the first clear solution candidate has been obtained, the group members can start to endorse this solution and refrain from further deliberation.",
